#1000
The Darkening Path~
The trail here narrows and the air itself seems to curdle, thick with a reek of damp decay that no breeze ever quite disperses.  To the west the familiar confusion-mist of the outer forest still clings in pale curtains, offering a murky path back to the disorienting but comparatively wholesome woodland beyond.  Eastward the trees grow immediately more twisted, their @@bbark@@N split lengthwise by veins of @@pfungal growth@@N that pulse with a faint, cold luminescence utterly unlike natural light.  Massive root knuckles have heaved the path apart, and dark footprints of something large press the soft soil in a pattern that makes the stomach turn, each print sinking deeper than any animal's weight should allow.  The canopy knits shut above, and the already-dim daylight that filters through carries a sickly violet tint, as though the corruption that pervades this place has stained even the air between the leaves.~
