The Crumbling Archway~
This was once the entrance to something, though what structure once rose here is lost — only the arch remains, its twin pillars of fitted stone leaning toward each other at precarious angles, the keystone above still somehow holding everything in place through blind habit.  @@pFungal colonies@@N have colonised every crack, and the stone itself has taken on the purple-grey colour of deep decay, crumbling at the edges like stale bread.  The crumbling arch frames a shaft of absolute darkness descending into the earth, from which rises a slow exhalation of cold, mineral-smelling air mixed with the unmistakable reek of deep fungus.  Scratched into the left pillar in hasty, uneven strokes is a single word: BELOW.  A corroded iron key, long since dropped and forgotten, might open whatever holds this arch closed — whoever left that warning clearly did not plan to return.~
