#1014
The Ruined Watchpost~
The remains of a wooden watchtower cling to a massive blighted oak here, its platform rotted away but the climbing rungs still nailed to the trunk in a series of iron spikes driven straight into the heartwood.  The oak itself is enormous — easily ten feet across at the base — and its canopy, dead but intact, spreads above in a dense ceiling of interlocked black branches that would have given whoever climbed here a view of the surrounding treetops.  A carved wooden sign still hangs from one rung, swinging slightly despite the absence of wind, and while its face is mostly eaten by rot, a compass rose is still faintly visible, pointing directions that no longer seem to correspond to anything trustworthy.  Below the sign, scratched into the bark of the oak with a knife blade: 'She is awake and she knows you are here.'  The air around the post is noticeably colder than elsewhere in the forest, and the silence here has a weight to it, a quality of being listened to from above.~
