A slightly wider clearing in the dense Blightwood marks the base of one of the oldest trees in this section — its trunk wider than three people could link arms around, its bark entirely dead but preserved by the fungal crust that coats it, its root-system surfacing in a ring of massive arches that create a natural enclosure.  From the branches above, far overhead, something that might be a crude rope ladder descends within arm's reach — its lower rungs rotted, but higher rungs still holding.  The canopy above is accessible from here, the massive branches of the ancient tree forming a highway into the elevated realm of the Ancient Canopy.~
