#1065
The Oozing Bark Corridor~
The trees lining this forest corridor are in an advanced state of corruption — their bark has separated from the wood beneath and hangs in long, curling strips, each one coated on the underside with a thick layer of @@pfungal matter@@N that oozes a slow, dark fluid.  The fluid drips from each strip in long pendant drops, and the forest floor beneath is black and slick with accumulated drip.  Navigation requires avoiding the drip-points, which is difficult given their density — a few minutes of standing still results in coverage of exposed skin.  The fluid is not immediately painful.  It is, however, persistent.~
