#1066
The Crooked Cathedral~
The trees here have grown so tall and so close together that their upper branches have intertwined far overhead in a vault of black wood — an accidental gothic cathedral roofed in dead interlocking timber.  The scale is genuine: the vault is sixty feet up, and the sound within the cathedral-space is different from the open forest, absorbed by the wood above into a deep, attentive silence.  The @@pcorruption@@N has given the wood a slight phosphorescent quality, and the vault above glows very faintly purple, casting a light that is more felt than seen.  Standing here at the intersection of several paths, it is easy to understand why something large might have chosen this spot as its territory.~
