#1067
The Blackened Understory~
The understory plants here — those that grow in the shadow of the main canopy — have all died and blackened but not fallen, creating a secondary layer of dark dead vegetation below the tree canopy.  The dead understory makes movement through this section difficult, the dry blackened stalks snapping loudly and showering black dust on anything that disturbs them.  The dust is mildly irritating to eyes and throat, and it settles on everything that passes through in a layer that takes hours to brush off.  Something has beaten a clear path through the understory that is wide enough for two — the stalks here are crushed, not snapped, pressed flat by considerable weight.~
