#1068
The Frozen Moment~
Something violent happened here long ago, and the forest has preserved the evidence with perfect fidelity in the deep-blight manner of this place.  Three trees are shattered at mid-height, their upper sections gone, their fractured bases splayed outward in a pattern consistent with a single enormous outward force.  Whatever caused it left no tracks, no debris, and no heat — the shattering happened in cold, and the cold of it lingers.  The @@dfractured wood@@N at each break has been colonised by a grey-white fungus that has rendered the surfaces sterile, and nothing grows within twenty feet of the largest shattered trunk.~
