#1071
The Pale Fungus Stand~
An unusual clustering of pale, non-bioluminescent fungi occupies the forest floor here — each specimen large, white-capped, and growing from a shared underground network that makes them sway in synchrony when the ground is disturbed nearby.  The fungi are enormous by surface standards: the largest cap spans six feet, and the cluster extends for fifty feet in all directions.  They are the only organisms in this section of the Blightwood that are not purple-grey-black in colour, and the white of them against the dark surroundings has an uncanny quality, as if they belong in a different forest.~
