#1072
The Woven Root Barrier~
A natural barrier of above-ground roots has grown across this section of the forest over years, creating a wall chest-height and several feet thick that forces passage to specific gaps where the root-weave is thinner.  The barrier runs roughly east to west as far as can be seen in either direction, and the gaps through it show signs of heavy use — the root-surfaces around them are worn smooth.  Beyond the barrier to the south, the forest character changes: the trees are more densely spaced and the darkness more complete, hinting at the deeper corruption of the Blightwood's interior.~
