#1073
The Resin Pools~
Pools of hardened and semi-liquid tree resin have accumulated on the forest floor here, leaking from trees whose cortex layers have been compromised by the fungal network within.  The hardened pools create irregular stepping-stone paths through the semi-liquid sections, and the semi-liquid resin is amber-coloured, sweet-smelling, and sticky enough to catch small creatures that wander in.  Several have been caught — visible at various depths in the hardening resin, preserved in exactly the posture of their final moment.  The trees above leak continuously, replenishing the pools on a timescale of days.~
